BREAKING #19: VirtualApplicationGroupResource.GetStartMenuItems renamed
================================================================================
Affected:
  - VirtualApplicationGroupResource.GetStartMenuItems(int?, bool?, int?, CancellationToken)
  - VirtualApplicationGroupResource.GetStartMenuItemsAsync(int?, bool?, int?, CancellationToken)

Root cause: Renamed to GetAll/GetAllAsync on a new StartMenuItems sub-collection.
The existing custom shim has a recursive call bug.

Fix: [SDK]
  Fix the existing custom code in src/Customize/VirtualApplicationGroupResource.cs.
  The current code calls itself recursively (bug). It should call the new
  GetAll method instead. Also add the full-parameter overload:

    [EditorBrowsable(EditorBrowsableState.Never)]
    public virtual Pageable<DesktopVirtualizationStartMenuItem> GetStartMenuItems(
        int? pageSize = null, bool? isDescending = null, int? initialSkip = null,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)
        => GetStartMenuItemCollection().GetAll(pageSize, isDescending, initialSkip, cancellationToken);

