BREAKING #21: PrivateEndpointConnection operation input type changed
================================================================================
Affected (DesktopVirtualizationPrivateEndpointConnection -> ...DataData):
  - HostPoolPrivateEndpointConnectionCollection.CreateOrUpdate(WaitUntil, string,
      DesktopVirtualizationPrivateEndpointConnection, CancellationToken)
  - HostPoolPrivateEndpointConnectionCollection.CreateOrUpdateAsync(same)
  - HostPoolPrivateEndpointConnectionResource.Update(WaitUntil,
      DesktopVirtualizationPrivateEndpointConnection, CancellationToken)
  - HostPoolPrivateEndpointConnectionResource.UpdateAsync(same)
  - WorkspacePrivateEndpointConnectionCollection.CreateOrUpdate(same)
  - WorkspacePrivateEndpointConnectionCollection.CreateOrUpdateAsync(same)
  - WorkspacePrivateEndpointConnectionResource.Update(same)
  - WorkspacePrivateEndpointConnectionResource.UpdateAsync(same)

Root cause: The input type changed from DesktopVirtualizationPrivateEndpointConnection
to DesktopVirtualizationPrivateEndpointConnectionDataData.

Fix: [SDK]
  Add backward-compat overloads that accept the old type and convert:

    [EditorBrowsable(EditorBrowsableState.Never)]
    public virtual ArmOperation<HostPoolPrivateEndpointConnectionResource>
        CreateOrUpdate(WaitUntil waitUntil, string name,
            DesktopVirtualizationPrivateEndpointConnection connection,
            CancellationToken cancellationToken = default)
    {
        // Convert DesktopVirtualizationPrivateEndpointConnection to
        // DesktopVirtualizationPrivateEndpointConnectionDataData and forward
    }

  Note: DesktopVirtualizationPrivateEndpointConnection needs public ctor
  (see Breaking #9). The conversion logic depends on the property mapping
  between the two types.

================================================================================
BREAKING #22: DesktopVirtualizationPrivateEndpointConnectionDataData properties
================================================================================
Affected:
  - ...DataData.ConnectionState.get (was DesktopVirtualizationPrivateLinkServiceConnectionState)
  - ...DataData.ConnectionState.set (same)
  - ...DataData.PrivateEndpointId.get (was Azure.Core.ResourceIdentifier)

Root cause:
  - "ConnectionState" was renamed to "PrivateLinkServiceConnectionState"
  - "PrivateEndpointId" type changed from ResourceIdentifier to string

Fix: [SDK]
  Add backward-compat properties in custom partial class:

    public partial class DesktopVirtualizationPrivateEndpointConnectionDataData
    {
        [Obsolete("Use PrivateLinkServiceConnectionState instead.")]
        [EditorBrowsable(EditorBrowsableState.Never)]
        public DesktopVirtualizationPrivateLinkServiceConnectionState ConnectionState
        {
            get => PrivateLinkServiceConnectionState;
            set => PrivateLinkServiceConnectionState = value;
        }

        // PrivateEndpointId is string, but old API returned ResourceIdentifier
        // Need a property with the old type
    }

  For PrivateEndpointId type change (string -> ResourceIdentifier), use [TSP]:
    @@alternateType(PrivateEndpointConnectionProperties.privateEndpoint.id,
        Azure.Core.armResourceIdentifier, "csharp");

================================================================================
BREAKING #23: DesktopVirtualizationPrivateEndpointConnection properties
================================================================================
Affected:
  - ConnectionState.get (renamed to PrivateLinkServiceConnectionState)
  - ConnectionState.set (same + type is now read-only)
  - PrivateEndpointId.get (type changed from ResourceIdentifier to string)

Same fix approach as Breaking #22. Note this is the Models type (not DataData).
Since this type has internal ctor (Breaking #9), properties are all read-only.

Fix: [SDK]
  Add backward-compat read-only property "ConnectionState" in partial class.
  For PrivateEndpointId type, same TSP fix as #22.

